        "spec": {
          "id": 6,
          "title": "Avg. CPU IO Wait Time",
          "description": "This metric shows how much time the CPU spends waiting on input/output devices to gain information. For example, the user inputs a USB drive. The file reader would first need to read the contents on the file before the CPU can interpret and process that data. The CPU would spend time doing nothing in that case. Because it can't process without that information\n",
          "links": [],
          "data": {
